cs.MA, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.NE

Reasoning: 

- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a likely category as the paper presents a model of metapopulations, which can be seen as a system of interacting agents.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper describes a simulation algorithm (tau-DPP) used to model the metapopulations.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper investigates the influence of network topologies on the dynamics of metapopulations, which can be seen as a type of network.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper applies computational methods to study ecological systems.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper describes a stochastic model of population dynamics, which can be related to evolutionary processes.
